Class TypeManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.energyxxer.commodore.types.defaults.TypeManager
  • public class TypeManager
extends java.lang.Object

      • createDictionary

        public TypeDictionary<?> createDictionary​(java.lang.String category,
                                          boolean useNamespace)
        Creates a dictionary for the specified category, and adds it to this type manager. The type this new dictionary will create is of the class GenericType.
        If the category specified already exists in this type manager, that will be returned instead.
        Parameters:
        category - The case-sensitve category string that represents types created by the new dictionary.
        useNamespace - Whether the types created by the new dictionary should be printed onto commands with the namespace: prefix. true if it should, false if it shouldn't. If the specified category already exists in this type manager, this parameter will have no effect.
        Returns:
        The dictionary for the specified category. If the category exists before the method call, that will be returned. Otherwise, a new dictionary is created and returned.

      • getDictionary

        public TypeDictionary<?> getDictionary​(java.lang.String category)
        Retrieves a dictionary for a specified category.
        Parameters:
        category - The category whose dictionary is to be returned.
        Returns:
        The type dictionary for the specified category, if it exists. null if it doesn't exist.
